            "answer_text": "Well for starters they can't be LGB and T. Decide which one. Don't use the term community, there isn't one. If they're a gay man give them a boyfriend. If it doesn't suit your story for them to have a partner don't mention their sexuality at all. JK Rowling said Dumbledore (sp?) was gay after the books finished. You can leave it up to the reader. Don't use cheap and tacky devices that relate to stereotypes. ",
